    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7299d2f8_fce3a955",
        "filename": "distrib/android-emugl/host/libs/Translator/include/GLcommon/GLIssue.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 17,
      "author": {
        "id": 1058003
      },
      "writtenOn": "2015-03-04T19:24:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I made this change early on, when I had a hard time telling apart when dispatch refers to libGL or the translator libraries. For a newbie, this was confusing. The rationale follows the parlance common in processor design: instructions (GLES calls) get dispatched when scheduled for execution; we only say they are \"issued\" (GL calls) when they are arrive at the execution units (in our case, libGL). \n\nIn retrospect, this was unnecessary to make it to this commit. As long as the distinction between GL_Dispatch (libGL API) and GLES_Dispatch (GLES_?? API) is clear, I am happy --- the prefix should be enough. I will abandon this change and stick to current naming, only making any changes necessary to ensure the prefix is consistent with the API it refers to.",
      "parentUuid": "929c86d9_10630a8f",
      "revId": "0225b47af3eddd97bc18c285b858afbe7be7e1c1",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
